title: For Sale:  Marlin .375 Winchester Lever Action
postcontent:
Marlin .375 Winchester Lever Action. Manufactured in 1980 this rifle is designed for one of the more powerful cartridges used in a lever-action rifle, .375 Winchester. Based on the Model 336C, the Model 375 was meant to be a rifle that could be used to hunt in forests and heavy brush, without being stopped by the vegetation. The action is similar to that of the Model 336C along with the same barrel length, and the stock has a pistol grip wrist. It is outfitted with a receiver sight which is sufficient for a range up to 100 yds. but shots beyond 150 yds. are not for the average hunter.More photos are available, send me a note for a link.
This rifle is in very good condition with minimal use and minor wear. The is a dent in the forearm, a spot of rust on the barrel, note that the front sight blade is not a perfect fit for the ramp, there is some evidence of wear on the front sight ramp, slight ding in the stock where it meets the butt pad but I guess most folks wouldn’t notice. Photos of all of the above are available. The bull’s eye in the stock is a replacement for the original which was missing for several years.
I will provide what ammo I have. A set of dies (not the exact ones pictured) with brass and bullets will be shipped free of charge from this guns original home. Local sales unless you’re prepared to figure out and pay for shipping. I assume shipping will be very expensive.
